The paper deals with content-based image retrieval, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV). The use of clustering algorithms for grouping images into meaningful categories suggests a focus on unsupervised learning (cs.IR), and the use of color moment and block truncation coding as feature extraction techniques suggests a focus on multimedia (cs.MM). Additionally, the use of K-Means clustering algorithm suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) and data mining (cs.DS).
